1. Install nodeJS (globally in ur pc)
	- before installing nodeJS check first if it is already installed in ur pc 
		- in CMD ? node -v
		- if installed then u will receive the version number
	- Otherwise install nodeJS
		- Go to https://nodejs.org/en/download/  & install nodejs (default)

2. Install Angular Cli (globally in ur pc)
	- in CMD ? npm install -g @angular/cli
3. Create Project
	- Create your AngularJS workspace
	- in your workspace, create angularJS project using CMD or GitBash
		- ng new <project-name> 
			- angularJS project will be created using this folder name
	- Open a browser with ur local host
		- gitBash/CMD in ur project folder and 
		     - ng serve --open
				- will open a browser with ur localhost home page (if 			        not opened go to the next line)
		     - if not opended, open any browser and
				- http://localhost:4200/
		      
